						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kulōttuṅga. Year 36: A.D. 1106.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to record an undertaking by the <hi rend="italic">śiva-brāhmaṇas</hi> of the temple of Tirumayāṉamuḍaiya Paramasvāmi at Nālūr in Chēṟṟūrkkūṟṟam, a subdivision of Kulōttuṅgachōḻa-vaḷanāḍu to maintain eight lamps daily on receipt of money from an individual Dēvabhaṭṭaṉ.</p>						

